  "text": "The LibreOffice document model architecture is built on a hierarchy of document shell and document classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx): The foundational base class for all SFx-objects/documents in LibreOffice. This class provides the core framework that all document types inherit from, managing document lifecycle, persistence, and inter-object communication.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx): The Writer (word processor) document class that represents a text document in LibreOffice Writer. It inherits from the document framework and manages text content, formatting, styles, and Writer-specific functionality.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class that manages spreadsheet data, cells, formulas, sheets, and Calc-specific operations for LibreOffice Calc.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx): The Impress/Draw document class that extends FmFormModel and manages presentation/drawing content including slides, shapes, animations, and form controls for LibreOffice Impress and Draw.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx): The LibreOffice application framework entry point and main application shell class. This class inherits from SfxShell and provides the top-level application management, handling global services, macros, event dispatching, and application-wide configuration.\n\nThe architecture follows a clear hierarchy where SfxObjectShell serves as the common base for all document types (Writer, Calc, Impress/Draw), while SfxApplication provides the containing framework that manages all document instances and application-level services."
}

